{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775875213856,"sessionID":"ses_2859701edffeUJTW0BpL9de1DF","part":{"id":"prt_d7a694a1b001x3EqRGKWn5h4sX","messageID":"msg_d7a694388001oR79r4P03JHKJB","sessionID":"ses_2859701edffeUJTW0BpL9de1DF","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875284456,"sessionID":"ses_2859701edffeUJTW0BpL9de1DF","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6a5d8d001x9uVz7Ez8oaOsv","messageID":"msg_d7a694388001oR79r4P03JHKJB","sessionID":"ses_2859701edffeUJTW0BpL9de1DF","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-04383aac9fa24b8a9aa6a4d7d41f930c","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Delta Specification: AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement dual provider support in the AgentCube CLI for deploying AI agents to Kubernetes: a standard provider using native Deployment and Service resources, and an AgentCube provider using the AgentRuntime custom resource (CR) for enhanced lifecycle management.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Provider selection via CLI flag\n\nThe system SHALL allow users to select the deployment target provider using the `--provider` flag on relevant commands (`publish`, `status`, `invoke`), with `agentcube` as the default provider.\n\n#### Scenario: Default provider value\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `publish` without the `--provider` flag\n- **WHEN** the Typer command callback runs\n- **THEN** the `provider` parameter SHALL default to `\"agentcube\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Valid provider selection\n- **GIVEN** the user specifies `--provider k8s` or `--provider agentcube`\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL route deployment operations to `KubernetesProvider` for `k8s` or `AgentCubeProvider` for `agentcube`\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid provider value\n- **GIVEN** the user specifies `--provider invalid`\n- **WHEN** the command validates the provider parameter\n- **THEN** the system SHALL print an error message indicating valid options are `k8s` or `agentcube` and exit with code `1`\n\n### Requirement: Kubernetes provider — Deployment creation\n\nThe system SHALL create a Kubernetes `Deployment` resource with configurable replicas, container port, and optional environment variables when using the `k8s` provider.\n\n#### Scenario: Minimal deployment creation\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s`, `replicas` is `1` (default), and no env_vars are provided\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` is called with `agent_name`, `image_url`, and `port`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create a Deployment with:\n  - `metadata.name` sanitized from `agent_name` via `_sanitize_name`\n  - `spec.replicas` set to `1`\n  - `spec.template.spec.containers[0].image` set to `image_url`\n  - `spec.template.spec.containers[0].ports[0].containerPort` set to `port`\n  - No environment variables in the container spec\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment with replicas and env vars\n- **GIVEN** `replicas` is `3` and `env_vars` is `{\"API_KEY\": \"secret\", \"DEBUG\": \"true\"}`\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create a Deployment with `spec.replicas` set to `3` and container `env` array containing both key-value pairs\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment with custom entrypoint\n- **GIVEN** `entrypoint` is `[\"python\", \"-u\", \"main.py\"]`\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` is called\n- **THEN** the container spec SHALL set `command` to the provided list\n\n#### Scenario: Name sanitization for K8s compliance\n- **GIVEN** `agent_name` is `my-agent-prod_v2.0`\n- **WHEN** `_sanitize_name` processes the name\n- **THEN** the result SHALL conform to Kubernetes naming rules (lowercase alphanumeric, hyphens, max 253 chars), e.g., `my-agent-prod-v2-0`\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace creation\n- **GIVEN** `namespace` is provided and does not exist\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider` initializes or deploys\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `_ensure_namespace` which creates the namespace if missing via the Kubernetes API\n\n### Requirement: Kubernetes provider — Service creation\n\nThe system SHALL create a NodePort Service exposing the deployment, with either a user-specified NodePort or an auto-assigned port in the valid range.\n\n#### Scenario: Service with user-specified NodePort\n- **GIVEN** `node_port` is `30080`\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider._create_service` is called\n- **THEN** the Service SHALL have `spec.ports[0].nodePort` set to `30080`\n\n#### Scenario: Service with auto-assigned NodePort\n- **GIVEN** `node_port` is `None`\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider._create_service` is called\n- **THEN** the Service SHALL omit the `nodePort` field, allowing Kubernetes to auto-assign a port in the 30000-32767 range\n\n#### Scenario: Service selector matches deployment\n- **GIVEN** the deployment was created with sanitized name `my-agent`\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider._create_service` runs\n- **THEN** the Service SHALL have `spec.selector` matching the deployment labels, typically including `app: my-agent`\n\n#### Scenario: Service URL construction\n- **GIVEN** the Service has `nodePort` `30080`\n- **WHEN** deployment completes successfully\n- **THEN** the result SHALL include `service_url` as `http://localhost:30080`\n\n### Requirement: Kubernetes provider — Rollout readiness\n\nThe system SHALL wait for the deployment to reach a ready state before considering the deployment complete, with a configurable timeout.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful rollout within timeout\n- **GIVEN** the deployment is created and pods become ready within 60 seconds\n- **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready(name=\"my-agent\", timeout=120)` is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return without error after all replicas are ready\n\n#### Scenario: Rollout timeout\n- **GIVEN** the deployment fails to become ready after 120 seconds\n- **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready(name=\"my-agent\", timeout=120)` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `TimeoutError` indicating the deployment did not become ready in time\n\n#### Scenario: Readiness polling\n- **GIVEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready` is polling\n- **WHEN** checking deployment status\n- **THEN** the system SHALL query the deployment status every 2 seconds and check that `status.readyReplicas` equals `spec.replicas`\n\n### Requirement: Kubernetes provider — Status retrieval\n\nThe system SHALL retrieve and report deployment status including replica counts, pod states, and service URL when using the `k8s` provider.\n\n#### Scenario: Running deployment status\n- **GIVEN** a deployment with 3 replicas is running, all pods are ready, and service has NodePort 30080\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status(agent_name)` is called\n- **THEN** the result SHALL include:\n  - `status: \"running\"`\n  - `replicas: 3`\n  - `ready_replicas: 3`\n  - `available_replicas: 3`\n  - `node_port: 30080`\n  - `service_url: \"http://localhost:30080\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment with unavailable pods\n- **GIVEN** a deployment with 2 replicas has 1 ready and 1 `CrashLoopBackOff`\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status` is called\n- **THEN** the result SHALL include `status: \"degraded\"` or `\"partial\"` and indicate the pod states\n\n#### Scenario: Non-existent deployment\n- **GIVEN** no deployment exists for `agent_name`\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status` is called\n- **THEN** the result SHALL include `status: \"not_found\"`\n\n### Requirement: Kubernetes provider — Deletion\n\nThe system SHALL delete both the Deployment and Service resources when removing an agent deployed via the `k8s` provider.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful deletion\n- **GIVEN** a deployment and service exist for `agent_name`\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.delete_agent(agent_name)` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL delete both resources and return `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\": <sanitized-name>, \"namespace\": <namespace>}`\n\n#### Scenario: Partial deletion tolerance\n- **GIVEN** only the Service exists (Deployment already deleted)\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.delete_agent` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL delete the Service, ignore the 404 error for the Deployment, and return success\n\n### Requirement: AgentCube provider — AgentRuntime CR creation\n\nThe system SHALL create or update an AgentRuntime custom resource in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group when using the `agentcube` provider.\n\n#### Scenario: Minimal AgentRuntime creation\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` and metadata contains `image_url` and `port`\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create an AgentRuntime CR with:\n  - `metadata.name` sanitized from `agent_name`\n  - `spec.image` set to `image_url`\n  - `spec.port` set to `port`\n  - `spec.sessionTimeout` set to `\"15m\"`\n  - `spec.maxSessionDuration` set to `\"8h\"`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime with readiness probe\n- **GIVEN** metadata includes `readiness_probe_path: \"/health\"` and `readiness_probe_port: 8080`\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` is called\n- **THEN** the CR SHALL include `spec.readinessProbe` with `httpGet.path: \"/health\"` and `httpGet.port: 8080`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime with custom env vars\n- **GIVEN** `env_vars` is `{\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\": \"http://wm:8080\", \"ROUTER_URL\": \"http://router:8080\"}`\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` is called\n- **THEN** the CR SHALL include these in `spec.env`\n\n#### Scenario: Auto-inject WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL and ROUTER_URL\n- **GIVEN** `env_vars` is `None` but `workload_manager_url` and `router_url` parameters are provided\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL inject `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` and `ROUTER_URL` into `spec.env` from the parameters or environment variables\n\n#### Scenario: Image pull secret configuration\n- **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime CR is being created\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` runs\n- **THEN** the CR SHALL include `spec.imagePullSecrets: [{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace creation for AgentCube provider\n- **GIVEN** `namespace` is provided and does not exist\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider` initializes or deploys\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `_ensure_namespace` which creates the namespace if missing\n\n### Requirement: AgentCube provider — AgentRuntime update\n\nThe system SHALL support updating an existing AgentRuntime CR when re-publishing, using strategic merge patch.\n\n#### Scenario: Update existing CR\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime CR exists for `agent_name` with `image: \"old:v1\"`\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime` is called with a new `image_url: \"new:v2\"`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL patch the existing CR with the new image while preserving other fields\n\n#### Scenario: Update with readiness probe addition\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime CR without a readiness probe\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime` is called with `readiness_probe_path` and `readiness_probe_port`\n- **THEN** the patched CR SHALL include the new `readinessProbe` configuration\n\n### Requirement: AgentCube provider — Status retrieval\n\nThe system SHALL retrieve AgentRuntime status from the CR's `status` field, reporting agent endpoint and runtime state.\n\n#### Scenario: Running AgentRuntime with status\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime CR exists with `status.phase: \"Running\"` and `status.agentEndpoint: \"http://service:8080\"`\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` is called\n- **THEN** the result SHALL include:\n  - `status: \"running\"`\n  - `agent_endpoint: \"http://service:8080\"`\n  - `phase: \"Running\"`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime created but no status yet\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime CR exists but has no `status` field populated yet\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` is called\n- **THEN** the result SHALL include `status: \"created_no_status\"`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime not found\n- **GIVEN** no AgentRuntime CR exists for `agent_name`\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` is called\n- **THEN** the result SHALL include `status: \"not_found_in_k8s\"`\n\n### Requirement: Publish runtime — Provider routing\n\nThe system SHALL route `publish` command operations to the appropriate provider class based on the `--provider` flag.\n\n#### Scenario: Publish with k8s provider\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `publish --provider k8s` with valid workspace and image\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `PublishRuntime._publish_k8s` which uses `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent`\n\n#### Scenario: Publish with agentcube provider\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `publish --provider agentcube` with valid workspace and image\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s` which uses `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime`\n\n#### Scenario: Publish image preparation for k8s\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s` and `image_url` is provided\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._prepare_image_for_publishing` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the provided `image_url` directly for Kubernetes deployment\n\n#### Scenario: Publish image preparation for agentcube\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` and `build_mode` is `local`\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._prepare_image_for_publishing` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL either push the local image to a registry or use the local image URL depending on configuration\n\n### Requirement: Status runtime — Provider routing\n\nThe system SHALL route `status` command queries to the appropriate provider class based on the `--provider` flag and deployment type.\n\n#### Scenario: Status with k8s provider\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `status --provider k8s`\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status` executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status` which uses `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status`\n\n#### Scenario: Status with agentcube provider\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `status --provider agentcube`\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status` executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` which uses `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime`\n\n#### Scenario: Auto-detect provider from metadata\n- **GIVEN** metadata has `k8s_deployment.type: \"AgentRuntime\"` and user runs `status` without `--provider`\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status` executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL automatically use the AgentCube provider path\n\n### Requirement: Invoke runtime — Provider routing\n\nThe system SHALL route `invoke` command HTTP requests based on the agent's deployment type and provider, using appropriate URL patterns.\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke with k8s provider\n- **GIVEN** the agent was deployed with `provider=k8s` and has `node_port: 30080`\n- **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs with `provider=\"k8s\"`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `_direct_http_invocation` targeting `http://localhost:30080` with the JSON payload\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke with agentcube provider and CR endpoint\n- **GIVEN** the agent was deployed with `provider=agentcube` and metadata has `agent_endpoint: \"http://service:8080\"`\n- **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs with `provider=\"agentcube\"`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` targeting the agent endpoint with session header\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke URL rewrite for AgentRuntime\n- **GIVEN** metadata has `k8s_deployment.type: \"AgentRuntime\"` and base endpoint from metadata\n- **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime._invoke_agent_via_agentcube` constructs the URL\n- **THEN** the system SHALL rewrite to `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n\n#### Scenario: Session header inclusion\n- **GIVEN** metadata contains `session_id: \"abc123\"`\n- **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` sends the request\n- **THEN** the HTTP headers SHALL include `X-Agentcube-Session-Id: abc123`\n\n### Requirement: Error handling for provider operations\n\nThe system SHALL provide clear error messages for provider-specific failures, including K8s API errors, missing CRDs, and invalid configurations.\n\n#### Scenario: Kubernetes client initialization failure\n- **GIVEN** the kubeconfig is invalid or cluster is unreachable\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider` or `AgentCubeProvider` initializes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise a descriptive error indicating Kubernetes connection failure and suggest checking kubeconfig\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime CRD not installed\n- **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime CRD is not installed in the cluster\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` attempts to create the CR\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise an error indicating the CRD is not found and suggest installing the AgentCube operator\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid NodePort range\n- **GIVEN** `node_port` is `40000` (outside 30000-32767)\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider._create_service` attempts to create the service\n- **THEN** Kubernetes API SHALL reject with validation error, which the system SHALL surface as a user-friendly message\n\n#### Scenario: Missing required AgentCube URLs\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` and metadata lacks `router_url` or `workload_manager_url`\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s` validates prerequisites\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` requiring both fields in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n### Requirement: Metadata updates after deployment\n\nThe system SHALL update workspace metadata with deployment information after successful publish operations, varying by provider.\n\n#### Scenario: K8s provider metadata update\n- **GIVEN** a deployment succeeds with `node_port: 30080`\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._update_publish_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** metadata SHALL be updated with:\n  - `k8s_deployment.type: \"Deployment\"`\n  - `k8s_deployment.name: <sanitized-name>`\n  - `k8s_deployment.namespace: <namespace>`\n  - `k8s_deployment.node_port: 30080`\n  - `k8s_deployment.service_url: \"http://localhost:30080\"`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentCube provider metadata update\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime CR is created successfully\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._update_publish_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** metadata SHALL be updated with:\n  - `k8s_deployment.type: \"AgentRuntime\"`\n  - `k8s_deployment.name: <sanitized-name>`\n  - `k8s_deployment.namespace: <namespace>`\n  - `agent_id: <cr-name>` (optional, if assigned by controller)\n\n### Requirement: Namespace parameter handling\n\nThe system SHALL support explicit namespace specification via `--namespace` flag for all provider operations, with intelligent defaults.\n\n#### Scenario: Explicit namespace for publish\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `publish --namespace production`\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL deploy to the `production` namespace\n\n#### Scenario: Default namespace when omitted\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `publish` without `--namespace`\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `default` namespace for both providers\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace consistency across commands\n- **GIVEN** an agent was published to namespace `staging`\n- **WHEN** user runs `status` or `invoke` without `--namespace`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL read the namespace from metadata's `k8s_deployment.namespace` field\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n1. **Kubernetes SDK**: The `kubernetes` Python package (v28.0.0+) is required for both providers. Use the provided client-go documentation for CR API reference.\n\n2. **Provider factory pattern**: `PublishRuntime` and `StatusRuntime` should instantiate the appropriate provider class based on the `provider` parameter:\n   ```python\n   if provider == \"k8s\":\n       provider_client = KubernetesProvider(namespace=namespace, verbose=verbose)\n   elif provider == \"agentcube\":\n       provider_client = AgentCubeProvider(namespace=namespace, verbose=verbose)\n   ```\n\n3. **Metadata-driven auto-detection**: When `provider` is not specified in `status` or `invoke`, read `k8s_deployment.type` from metadata to determine which provider to use.\n\n4. **Error context**: Provider-specific errors should include context about which provider was being used to aid debugging.\n\n5. **CR API constants**: For `AgentCubeProvider`, use:\n   - Group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n   - Version: `v1alpha1`\n   - Plural: `agentruntimes`\n\n6. **Testing considerations**: Mock both the Kubernetes API and custom resource API in unit tests. Test both happy paths and error conditions for each provider.","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775875284447,"end":1775875284453}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775875284483,"sessionID":"ses_2859701edffeUJTW0BpL9de1DF","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6a5de7001Xo7QzJ4REciNca","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7a694388001oR79r4P03JHKJB","sessionID":"ses_2859701edffeUJTW0BpL9de1DF","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":40216,"input":2773,"output":5124,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":32319}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775875285568,"sessionID":"ses_2859701edffeUJTW0BpL9de1DF","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6a623e001NTEAv9Ohm436nz","messageID":"msg_d7a6a5e1a0019sBC8YITY9dBBa","sessionID":"ses_2859701edffeUJTW0BpL9de1DF","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875286491,"sessionID":"ses_2859701edffeUJTW0BpL9de1DF","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6a65c7001emJTv1mu0PWOIs","messageID":"msg_d7a6a5e1a0019sBC8YITY9dBBa","sessionID":"ses_2859701edffeUJTW0BpL9de1DF","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-79da6e1e5b1d46bf987647f83821dc68","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification: AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型\n2: \n3: ## Module: `cmd/cli`\n4: \n5: ## Language: Python\n6: \n7: ## Size: M\n8: \n9: ## Delta Overview\n10: \n11: Enhance the `MetadataService` and related data models to support improved metadata validation, persistence, manipulation, and management capabilities for the AgentCube CLI. This includes enhanced field validation, schema versioning, metadata templates, history tracking, and security scanning.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## REQ-001: Enhanced metadata validation\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Comprehensive field validation beyond type checking\n18: \n19: System SHALL provide comprehensive validation for metadata fields including format validation, context-aware validation, and security checks.\n20: \n21: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n22: - Validates agent name follows DNS-1123 subdomain format\n23: - Validates entrypoint format based on language\n24: - Validates image URL format for container registries\n25: - Validates port range with context warnings for privileged ports\n26: - Provides clear, actionable error messages\n27: \n28: **Scenarios:**\n29: \n30: #### Scenario 1.1: Validate agent name format\n31: - **GIVEN** a metadata object with `agent_name` containing invalid characters\n32: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_agent_name` is called with `\"My Agent\"`\n33: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValidationError` with message explaining DNS-1123 subdomain format requirements\n34: \n35: #### Scenario 1.2: Valid agent name format\n36: - **GIVEN** a metadata object with `agent_name = \"my-agent-123\"`\n37: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_agent_name` is called\n38: - **THEN** the system SHALL pass validation without error\n39: \n40: #### Scenario 1.3: Validate Python entrypoint\n41: - **GIVEN** a metadata object with `language = \"python\"` and `entrypoint = \"python main.py\"`\n42: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_entrypoint` is called\n43: - **THEN** the system SHALL pass validation\n44: \n45: #### Scenario 1.4: Invalid Python entrypoint\n46: - **GIVEN** a metadata object with `language = \"python\"` and `entrypoint = \"javac Main.java\"`\n47: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_entrypoint` is called\n48: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValidationError` indicating mismatch between language and entrypoint\n49: \n50: #### Scenario 1.5: Validate Java entrypoint\n51: - **GIVEN** a metadata object with `language = \"java\"` and `entrypoint = \"java -jar app.jar\"`\n52: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_entrypoint` is called\n53: - **THEN** the system SHALL pass validation\n54: \n55: #### Scenario 1.6: Validate image URL format\n56: - **GIVEN** a metadata object with `image = {\"url\": \"registry.io/namespace/name:tag\"}`\n57: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_image_url` is called\n58: - **THEN** the system SHALL pass validation\n59: \n60: #### Scenario 1.7: Invalid image URL format\n61: - **GIVEN** a metadata object with `image = {\"url\": \"invalid-url-format\"}`\n62: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_image_url` is called\n63: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValidationError` with message explaining expected container image format\n64: \n65: #### Scenario 1.8: Validate privileged port\n66: - **GIVEN** a metadata object with `port = 80`\n67: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_port_context` is called\n68: - **THEN** the system SHALL pass validation AND log warning about privileged port requiring special permissions\n69: \n70: #### Scenario 1.9: Invalid port range\n71: - **GIVEN** a metadata object with `port = 70000`\n72: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_port_context` is called\n73: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValidationError` indicating port must be in range 1-65535\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## REQ-002: Metadata migration and versioning\n78: \n79: ### Requirement: Schema versioning with automatic migration support\n80: \n81: System SHALL support metadata schema versioning and automatic migration from previous versions.\n82: \n83: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n84: - Detects and reads schema version from metadata files\n85: - Applies automatic migrations for older schema versions\n86: - Preserves all valid fields during migration\n87: - Updates schema version after successful migration\n88: - Rejects metadata with unsupported future schema versions\n89: \n90: **Scenarios:**\n91: \n92: #### Scenario 2.1: Detect current schema version\n93: - **GIVEN** an existing `agent_metadata.yaml` with `schema_version = \"1.0.0\"`\n94: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` is called\n95: - **THEN** the system SHALL read the `schema_version` field and use it to determine migration needs\n96: \n97: #### Scenario 2.2: Default schema version for legacy files\n98: - **GIVEN** an existing `agent_metadata.yaml` without `schema_version` field\n99: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` is called\n100: - **THEN** the system SHALL default to version `\"0.0.0\"` (legacy) and apply migrations\n101: \n102: #### Scenario 2.3: Migrate from legacy format\n103: - **GIVEN** a metadata file with `schema_version < \"1.0.0\"`\n104: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` is called\n105: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n106:   - Apply automatic migrations to convert to current schema\n107:   - Preserve all valid fields\n108:   - Map deprecated field names to new ones\n109:   - Save the migrated metadata with updated `schema_version = \"1.0.0\"`\n110: \n111: #### Scenario 2.4: Migrate specific deprecated field\n112: - **GIVEN** a metadata file with `schema_version = \"0.5.0\"` containing deprecated field `agent_id_old`\n113: - **WHEN** migration runs\n114: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n115:   - Copy value from `agent_id_old` to `agent_id`\n116:   - Remove `agent_id_old` from migrated metadata\n117:   - Log the migration action\n118: \n119: #### Scenario 2.5: Reject unsupported future schema version\n120: - **GIVEN** a metadata file with `schema_version = \"2.0.0\"` (newer than supported)\n121: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` is called\n122: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `SchemaVersionError` indicating CLI needs to be upgraded\n123: \n124: #### Scenario 2.6: No migration for current schema\n125: - **GIVEN** a metadata file with `schema_version = \"1.0.0\"` (current version)\n126: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` is called\n127: - **THEN** the system SHALL load metadata without applying migrations\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ## REQ-003: Metadata merge and override\n132: \n133: ### Requirement: Robust merge capabilities for combining metadata sources\n134: \n135: System SHALL provide merge capabilities for combining base metadata from files with CLI option overrides.\n136: \n137: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n138: - Merges CLI options into existing metadata\n139: - Preserves fields not specified in CLI options\n140: - Validates merged result\n141: - Tracks which fields were overridden for logging\n142: - Handles conflicts appropriately\n143: \n144: **Scenarios:**\n145: \n146: #### Scenario 3.1: Merge with CLI overrides\n147: - **GIVEN** existing metadata with `agent_name = \"old-name\"` and CLI option `--agent-name new-name`\n148: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.merge_metadata` is called\n149: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n150:   - Apply CLI override: `agent_name = \"new-name\"`\n151:   - Preserve other fields not in CLI options\n152:   - Track that `agent_name` was overridden\n153: \n154: #### Scenario 3.2: Merge with multiple overrides\n155: - **GIVEN** existing metadata and CLI options for multiple fields\n156: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.merge_metadata` is called with `agent_name`, `port`, and `language` overrides\n157: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n158:   - Apply all CLI overrides\n159:   - Preserve all other fields\n160:   - Track all overridden fields\n161: \n162: #### Scenario 3.3: Merge with validation failure\n163: - **GIVEN** existing metadata and CLI options that conflict (e.g., language mismatch)\n164: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.merge_metadata` is called\n165: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n166:   - Attempt to merge the metadata\n167:   - Validate the merged result\n168:   - Raise `ValidationError` if merged metadata is invalid\n169: \n170: #### Scenario 3.4: Merge with partial overrides\n171: - **GIVEN** existing metadata with all fields populated\n172: - **WHEN** CLI provides only `--port 8080`\n173: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n174:   - Update only the `port` field\n175:   - Leave all other fields unchanged\n176: \n177: #### Scenario 3.5: Merge with new fields\n178: - **GIVEN** existing metadata and CLI options for fields not in metadata\n179: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.merge_metadata` is called\n180: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n181:   - Add the new fields from CLI options\n182:   - Preserve existing fields\n183:   - Validate the complete merged result\n184: \n185: ---\n186: \n187: ## REQ-004: Metadata templates and presets\n188: \n189: ### Requirement: Template system for common agent patterns\n190: \n191: System SHALL support metadata templates for common agent patterns and configurations.\n192: \n193: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n194: - Loads built-in templates for common patterns\n195: - Supports user-defined custom templates\n196: - Validates template completeness\n197: - Applies template defaults to new metadata\n198: - Allows customization after template application\n199: \n200: **Scenarios:**\n201: \n202: #### Scenario 4.1: Load built-in Python template\n203: - **GIVEN** template name `\"python-fastapi\"`\n204: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_template` is called\n205: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n206:   - Load the template from built-in template directory\n207:   - Return `AgentMetadata` with FastAPI-specific defaults:\n208:     - `language = \"python\"`\n209:     - `port = 8000`\n210:     - `entrypoint = \"uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port {port}\"`\n211: \n212: #### Scenario 4.2: Load built-in Java template\n213: - **GIVEN** template name `\"java-spring\"`\n214: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_template` is called\n215: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n216:   - Load the template from built-in template directory\n217:   - Return `AgentMetadata` with Spring Boot defaults:\n218:     - `language = \"java\"`\n219:     - `port = 8080`\n220:     - `entrypoint = \"java -jar app.jar\"`\n221: \n222: #### Scenario 4.3: Load user-defined template\n223: - **GIVEN** a user template file at `~/.agentcube/templates/my-custom-agent.yaml`\n224: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_template` is called with `\"my-custom-agent\"`\n225: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n226:   - Search user template directory first\n227:   - Load the template from user directory\n228:   - Return `AgentMetadata` with user-defined defaults\n229: \n230: #### Scenario 4.4: Template not found\n231: - **GIVEN** template name `\"nonexistent-template\"`\n232: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_template` is called\n233: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `TemplateNotFoundError` with helpful message\n234: \n235: #### Scenario 4.5: Validate template completeness\n236: - **GIVEN** a user-defined template file\n237: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_template` is called\n238: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n239:   - Verify template contains all required fields\n240:   - Warn about optional fields that should be provided by user\n241:   - Return validation result\n242: \n243: #### Scenario 4.6: Apply template to workspace\n244: - **GIVEN** a workspace without metadata\n245: - **WHEN** user runs `pack --template python-fastapi`\n246: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n247:   - Load the template\n248:   - Save it as initial metadata\n249:   - Allow user to customize fields via CLI options\n250: \n251: ---\n252: \n253: ## REQ-005: Metadata validation for deployment\n254: \n255: ### Requirement: Pre-deployment validation based on provider\n256: \n257: System SHALL validate metadata requirements specific to the deployment provider.\n258: \n259: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n260: - Validates AgentCube provider requirements\n261: - Validates Kubernetes provider requirements\n262: - Raises appropriate errors for missing required fields\n263: - Provides clear error messages with field names\n264: \n265: **Scenarios:**\n266: \n267: #### Scenario 5.1: Validate for AgentCube deployment\n268: - **GIVEN** metadata with `provider=\"agentcube\"`\n269: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_for_deployment` is called\n270: - **THEN** the system SHALL verify:\n271:   - `router_url` is present and valid URL\n272:   - `workload_manager_url` is present and valid URL\n273:   - `readiness_probe_path` is set\n274:   - `readiness_probe_port` is set\n275: \n276: #### Scenario 5.2: AgentCube deployment missing router_url\n277: - **GIVEN** metadata with `provider=\"agentcube\"` and no `router_url`\n278: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_for_deployment` is called\n279: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `DeploymentValidationError` indicating `router_url` is required\n280: \n281: #### Scenario 5.3: Validate for Kubernetes deployment\n282: - **GIVEN** metadata with `provider=\"k8s\"`\n283: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_for_deployment` is called\n284: - **THEN** the system SHALL verify:\n285:   - `image.url` is present and valid\n286:   - `image.tag` is present\n287:   - `port` is set and valid\n288:   - `namespace` is set if provided\n289: \n290: #### Scenario 5.4: Kubernetes deployment missing image URL\n291: - **GIVEN** metadata with `provider=\"k8s\"` and no `image.url`\n292: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_for_deployment` is called\n293: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `DeploymentValidationError` indicating image URL is required\n294: \n295: #### Scenario 5.5: Validate with all required fields present\n296: - **GIVEN** metadata with all required fields for the provider\n297: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_for_deployment` is called\n298: - **THEN** the system SHALL pass validation without error\n299: \n300: ---\n301: \n302: ## REQ-006: Metadata serialization and deserialization\n303: \n304: ### Requirement: Enhanced YAML serialization with comments and environment expansion\n305: \n306: System SHALL support multiple serialization formats with consistent behavior and helpful output.\n307: \n308: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n309: - Serializes to YAML with helpful comments\n310: - Excludes None values from output\n311: - Preserves field order\n312: - Supports environment variable expansion during deserialization\n313: - Provides consistent behavior across load/save operations\n314: \n315: **Scenarios:**\n316: \n317: #### Scenario 6.1: Serialize to YAML with comments\n318: - **GIVEN** an `AgentMetadata` object\n319: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` is called\n320: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n321:   - Write YAML with helpful comments for each field\n322:   - Exclude fields with `None` values\n323:   - Preserve field order from model definition\n324: \n325: #### Scenario 6.2: Deserialize with environment variable expansion\n326: - **GIVEN** a YAML file containing `registry_url: \"${REGISTRY_URL}\"`\n327: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` is called with `REGISTRY_URL=\"my-registry.io\"` in environment\n328: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n329:   - Expand `${REGISTRY_URL}` to `\"my-registry.io\"`\n330:   - Return metadata with `registry_url = \"my-registry.io\"`\n331: \n332: #### Scenario 6.3: Missing required environment variable\n333: - **GIVEN** a YAML file containing `registry_url: \"${REGISTRY_URL}\"`\n334: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` is called without `REGISTRY_URL` in environment\n335: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValidationError` indicating required environment variable is not set\n336: \n337: #### Scenario 6.4: Default value for missing environment variable\n338: - **GIVEN** a YAML file containing `registry_url: \"${REGISTRY_URL:-default-registry.io}\"`\n339: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` is called without `REGISTRY_URL` in environment\n340: - **THEN** the system SHALL use the default value `\"default-registry.io\"`\n341: \n342: #### Scenario 6.5: Preserve field order during save\n343: - **GIVEN** an `AgentMetadata` object with fields in specific order\n344: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` is called\n345: - **THEN** the system SHALL write fields in the same order as in the model definition\n346: \n347: #### Scenario 6.6: Exclude None values from output\n348: - **GIVEN** an `AgentMetadata` object with some optional fields set to `None`\n349: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` is called\n350: - **THEN** the system SHALL NOT write fields with `None` values to the YAML file\n351: \n352: ---\n353: \n354: ## REQ-007: Metadata history and rollback\n355: \n356: ### Requirement: Track metadata changes and support rollback\n357: \n358: System SHALL track metadata changes over time and support rollback to previous versions.\n359: \n360: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n361: - Creates backup of previous metadata before save\n362: - Stores backups with timestamps\n363: - Limits backup count to configurable maximum\n364: - Supports rollback to specific backup version\n365: - Lists available backup versions\n366: \n367: **Scenarios:**\n368: \n369: #### Scenario 7.1: Track metadata changes on save\n370: - **GIVEN** a workspace with existing metadata\n371: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` is called\n372: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n373:   - Create a backup of the previous metadata file\n374:   - Store backup in `.agentcube/metadata_history/` directory\n375:   - Use filename with timestamp: `agent_metadata_20250411_120000.yaml`\n376:   - Save new metadata as `agent_metadata.yaml`\n377: \n378: #### Scenario 7.2: Rollback to previous version\n379: - **GIVEN** multiple metadata backups exist\n380: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.rollback_metadata` is called with version `\"20250411_120000\"`\n381: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n382:   - Restore the specified backup to main metadata file\n383:   - Create a backup of current metadata before rolling back\n384:   - Update metadata with appropriate timestamp\n385: \n386: #### Scenario 7.3: List metadata history\n387: - **GIVEN** multiple metadata backups exist\n388: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.list_metadata_history` is called\n389: - **THEN** the system SHALL return:\n390:   - List of available backups with timestamps\n391:   - Indication of which backup is currently active\n392: \n393: #### Scenario 7.4: Limit backup count\n394: - **GIVEN** metadata history with 15 backups and default limit of 10\n395: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` is called\n396: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n397:   - Create new backup\n398:   - Remove oldest backup to maintain limit of 10\n399: \n400: #### Scenario 7.5: Configurable backup limit\n401: - **GIVEN** environment variable `AGENTCUBE_METADATA_HISTORY_LIMIT=5`\n402: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` is called\n403: - **THEN** the system SHALL maintain maximum 5 backups\n404: \n405: #### Scenario 7.6: No history directory on first save\n406: - **GIVEN** a workspace without `.agentcube/metadata_history/` directory\n407: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` is called\n408: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n409:   - Create the directory structure\n410:   - Save metadata without backup (no previous version exists)\n411: \n412: ---\n413: \n414: ## REQ-008: Metadata validation for security\n415: \n416: ### Requirement: Security best practices validation\n417: \n418: System SHALL validate metadata for security best practices and detect potential credential exposure.\n419: \n420: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n421: - Scans for potential credentials in metadata fields\n422: - Warns about storing credentials in plaintext\n423: - Validates registry credential configuration\n424: - Recommends environment variables for sensitive data\n425: \n426: **Scenarios:**\n427: \n428: #### Scenario 8.1: Detect API key pattern\n429: - **GIVEN** a metadata object with field containing text matching API key pattern\n430: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.scan_for_credentials` is called\n431: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n432:   - Detect potential API key\n433:   - Return list of fields containing potential credentials\n434:   - Log warning about credential exposure\n435: \n436: #### Scenario 8.2: Detect password pattern\n437: - **GIVEN** a metadata object with field containing `\"password\": \"secret123\"`\n438: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.scan_for_credentials` is called\n439: - **THEN** the system SHALL detect the password pattern and return warning\n440: \n441: #### Scenario 8.3: No credentials detected\n442: - **GIVEN** a metadata object without sensitive patterns\n443: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.scan_for_credentials` is called\n444: - **THEN** the system SHALL return empty list (no credentials found)\n445: \n446: #### Scenario 8.4: Validate registry credentials\n447: - **GIVEN** metadata with `registry_url` requiring authentication\n448: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_registry_credentials` is called\n449: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n450:   - Check if `registry_username` and `registry_password` are present\n451:   - Warn about storing credentials in plaintext\n452:   - Recommend using environment variables\n453: \n454: #### Scenario 8.5: Registry credentials missing when required\n455: - **GIVEN** metadata with `registry_url` pointing to private registry\n456: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_registry_credentials` is called\n457: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValidationError` indicating credentials are required\n458: \n459: #### Scenario 8.6: Recommend environment variables\n460: - **GIVEN** metadata with plaintext credentials\n461: - **WHEN** security scan detects credentials\n462: - **THEN** the system SHALL recommend:\n463:   - Using environment variables instead\n464:   - Example: `${REGISTRY_USERNAME}` instead of plaintext value\n465: \n466: ---\n467: \n468: ## Data Model Changes\n469: \n470: ### `AgentMetadata` enhancements\n471: \n472: Add new fields to `AgentMetadata`:\n473: \n474: | Field | Type | Default | Description |\n475: |-------|------|---------|-------------|\n476: | `schema_version` | `str` | `\"1.0.0\"` | Metadata schema version for migration support |\n477: | `template_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Name of template used to create this metadata |\n478: | `metadata_created_at` | `Optional[datetime]` | `None` | Timestamp when metadata was first created |\n479: | `metadata_updated_at` | `Optional[datetime]` | `None` | Timestamp of last metadata update |\n480: | `deployment_history` | `Optional[List[Dict[str, Any]]]` | `None` | Track deployment attempts and results |\n481: \n482: Add new validators:\n483: - `validate_agent_name_format` - DNS-1123 subdomain format validation\n484: - `validate_entrypoint_command` - Language-specific command validation\n485: - `validate_registry_url` - Container registry URL format validation\n486: - `validate_schema_version` - Schema version compatibility check\n487: \n488: ### `MetadataService` new methods\n489: \n490: ```python\n491: class MetadataService:\n492:     # Validation methods\n493:     def validate_agent_name(self, agent_name: str) -> None: ...\n494:     def validate_entrypoint(self, entrypoint: str, language: str) -> None: ...\n495:     def validate_image_url(self, image_url: str) -> None: ...\n496:     def validate_port_context(self, port: int) -> None: ...\n497: \n498:     # Schema versioning methods\n499:     def get_schema_version(self, workspace_path: Path) -> str: ...\n500:     def migrate_metadata(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, from_version: str) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n501: \n502:     # Merge methods\n503:     def merge_metadata(self, base: AgentMetadata, overrides: MetadataOptions) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n504: \n505:     # Template methods\n506:     def load_template(self, template_name: str) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n507:     def validate_template(self, template_path: Path) -> None: ...\n508:     def list_templates(self) -> List[str]: ...\n509: \n510:     # Deployment validation methods\n511:     def validate_for_deployment(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, provider: str) -> None: ...\n512: \n513:     # Serialization methods\n514:     def expand_env_vars(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n515: \n516:     # History methods\n517:     def backup_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Path: ...\n518:     def rollback_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, version: str) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n519:     def list_metadata_history(self, workspace_path: Path) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n520:     def cleanup_old_backups(self, workspace_path: Path, max_backups: int) -> None: ...\n521: \n522:     # Security methods\n523:     def scan_for_credentials(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> List[str]: ...\n524:     def validate_registry_credentials(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n525: ```\n526: \n527: ### New exception classes\n528: \n529: ```python\n530: class MetadataValidationError(ValidationError):\n531:     \"\"\"Raised when metadata validation fails\"\"\"\n532:     pass\n533: \n534: class SchemaVersionError(ValueError):\n535:     \"\"\"Raised when metadata schema version is incompatible\"\"\"\n536:     pass\n537: \n538: class DeploymentValidationError(MetadataValidationError):\n539:     \"\"\"Raised when metadata is invalid for deployment\"\"\"\n540:     pass\n541: \n542: class TemplateNotFoundError(FileNotFoundError):\n543:     \"\"\"Raised when a requested template is not found\"\"\"\n544:     pass\n545: ```\n546: \n547: ### Template directory structure\n548: \n549: ```\n550: ~/.agentcube/templates/\n551: ├── python-fastapi.yaml\n552: ├── python-flask.yaml\n553: ├── java-spring.yaml\n554: ├── java-quarkus.yaml\n555: └── custom/\n556:     └── (user-defined templates)\n557: ```\n558: \n559: ---\n560: \n561: ## Testing Requirements\n562: \n563: ### Unit Test Scenarios\n564: \n565: #### Scenario UT-1.1: Test validation methods\n566: - **GIVEN** a test suite for validation methods\n567: - **WHEN** tests run\n568: - **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n569:   - Valid and invalid agent name formats\n570:   - Valid and invalid entrypoint formats for each language\n571:   - Valid and invalid image URL formats\n572:   - Port range validation with privileged port warnings\n573: \n574: #### Scenario UT-1.2: Test schema migration\n575: - **GIVEN** a test suite for schema migration\n576: - **WHEN** tests run\n577: - **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n578:   - Migration from legacy to current schema\n579:   - Migration between multiple schema versions\n580:   - Field mapping during migration\n581:   - Schema version rejection for future versions\n582: \n583: #### Scenario UT-1.3: Test metadata merge\n584: - **GIVEN** a test suite for metadata merge\n585: - **WHEN** tests run\n586: - **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n587:   - Simple field override\n588:   - Multiple field overrides\n589:   - Merge with validation failure\n590:   - Partial overrides\n591:   - New field addition\n592: \n593: #### Scenario UT-1.4: Test template loading\n594: - **GIVEN** a test suite for template loading\n595: - **WHEN** tests run\n596: - **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n597:   - Loading built-in templates\n598:   - Loading user-defined templates\n599:   - Template not found error\n600:   - Template validation\n601: \n602: #### Scenario UT-1.5: Test deployment validation\n603: - **GIVEN** a test suite for deployment validation\n604: - **WHEN** tests run\n605: - **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n606:   - AgentCube provider validation\n607:   - Kubernetes provider validation\n608:   - Missing required fields\n609:   - Valid configuration\n610: \n611: #### Scenario UT-1.6: Test metadata history\n612: - **GIVEN** a test suite for metadata history\n613: - **WHEN** tests run\n614: - **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n615:   - Backup creation on save\n616:   - Rollback to specific version\n617:   - Listing history\n618:   - Backup count limits\n619: \n620: #### Scenario UT-1.7: Test security scanning\n621: - **GIVEN** a test suite for security scanning\n622: - **WHEN** tests run\n623: - **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n624:   - API key pattern detection\n625:   - Password pattern detection\n626:   - No credentials case\n627:   - Registry credential validation\n628: \n629: ### Integration Test Scenarios\n630: \n631: #### Scenario IT-1.1: End-to-end metadata lifecycle\n632: - **GIVEN** a new agent workspace\n633: - **WHEN** user runs:\n634:   1. `pack --template python-fastapi --agent-name my-agent`\n635:   2. Modifies metadata file\n636:   3. Runs `pack --port 9000`\n637: - **THEN** each operation SHALL:\n638:   - Use template for initial metadata\n639:   - Track changes in history\n640:   - Apply overrides correctly\n641:   - Validate all changes\n642: \n643: #### Scenario IT-1.2: Schema migration on existing workspace\n644: - **GIVEN** an existing workspace with legacy metadata\n645: - **WHEN** user runs `pack`\n646: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n647:   - Detect legacy schema\n648:   - Apply automatic migration\n649:   - Update schema version\n650:   - Log migration actions\n651: \n652: ---\n653: \n654: ## Acceptance Criteria\n655: \n656: ### Functional Acceptance Criteria - Metadata Validation\n657: \n658: - [ ] All validation methods accept valid inputs without error\n659: - [ ] All validation methods reject invalid inputs with clear error messages\n660: - [ ] Agent name validation enforces DNS-1123 subdomain format\n661: - [ ] Entrypoint validation is language-specific\n662: - [ ] Image URL validation enforces container registry format\n663: - [ ] Port validation includes context warnings for privileged ports\n664: \n665: ### Functional Acceptance Criteria - Schema Versioning\n666: \n667: - [ ] Schema version is detected from metadata files\n668: - [ ] Legacy files default to version \"0.0.0\"\n669: - [ ] Automatic migration works for at least 2 previous schema versions\n670: - [ ] Future schema versions are rejected with upgrade message\n671: - [ ] Migrated metadata has updated schema version\n672: \n673: ### Functional Acceptance Criteria - Metadata Merge\n674: \n675: - [ ] CLI options override metadata file values\n676: - [ ] Fields not in CLI options are preserved\n677: - [ ] Merged metadata is validated\n678: - [ ] Override tracking works for logging\n679: \n680: ### Functional Acceptance Criteria - Templates\n681: \n682: - [ ] Built-in templates load successfully\n683: - [ ] User-defined templates load from correct location\n684: - [ ] Missing templates raise appropriate error\n685: - [ ] Template validation works correctly\n686: - [ ] Template application creates valid metadata\n687: \n688: ### Functional Acceptance Criteria - Deployment Validation\n689: \n690: - [ ] AgentCube provider validates required fields\n691: - [ ] Kubernetes provider validates required fields\n692: - [ ] Missing required fields raise `DeploymentValidationError`\n693: - [ ] Valid configurations pass validation\n694: \n695: ### Functional Acceptance Criteria - Serialization\n696: \n697: - [ ] YAML output includes helpful comments\n698: - [ ] None values are excluded from output\n699: - [ ] Field order is preserved\n700: - [ ] Environment variables are expanded correctly\n701: - [ ] Missing environment variables raise `ValidationError`\n702: \n703: ### Functional Acceptance Criteria - History and Rollback\n704: \n705: - [ ] Backups are created before each save\n706: - [ ] Backup filenames include timestamps\n707: - [ ] Rollback restores specified version\n708: - [ ] History listing returns all backups\n709: - [ ] Backup count limits are enforced\n710: \n711: ### Functional Acceptance Criteria - Security\n712: \n713: - [ ] Credential scanning detects common patterns\n714: - [ ] Warnings are logged for detected credentials\n715: - [ ] Registry credential validation works correctly\n716: - [ ] Environment variable recommendations are provided\n717: \n718: ### Non-Functional Acceptance Criteria\n719: \n720: - [ ] Metadata operations complete within 100ms for typical workspaces\n721: - [ ] Validation error messages are clear and actionable\n722: - [ ] Migration process is backwards compatible\n723: - [ ] Template system is extensible for user-defined templates\n724: - [ ] History management is efficient (max 10 backups by default)\n725: - [ ] Unit tests cover all new methods with >= 90% coverage\n726: - [ ] Integration tests cover end-to-end workflows\n727: \n728: ---\n729: \n730: ## Implementation Notes\n731: \n732: ### Key Components\n733: \n734: 1. **MetadataService** (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n735:    - Enhanced with validation, migration, merge, template, history, and security methods\n736:    - Maintains backwards compatibility with existing methods\n737: \n738: 2. **AgentMetadata** (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n739:    - Extended with new fields for schema versioning, templates, timestamps, and history\n740:    - New validators for comprehensive field validation\n741: \n742: 3. **Template System** (`agentcube/templates/` and `~/.agentcube/templates/`)\n743:    - Built-in templates for common agent patterns\n744:    - Support for user-defined custom templates\n745: \n746: 4. **Metadata History** (`.agentcube/metadata_history/`)\n747:    - Automatic backup creation\n748:    - Timestamp-based versioning\n749:    - Configurable backup limits\n750: \n751: ### Key Algorithms\n752: \n753: #### Validation Algorithm\n754: 1. For each field requiring validation:\n755:    - Apply format-specific validation rules\n756:    - Check context-specific constraints (e.g., privileged ports)\n757:    - Raise `ValidationError` with descriptive message on failure\n758: \n759: #### Migration Algorithm\n760: 1. Read `schema_version` from metadata\n761: 2. If version < current version:\n762:    - Apply migration functions in sequence\n763:    - Map deprecated fields to new ones\n764:    - Update `schema_version` to current\n765: 3. If version > current version:\n766:    - Raise `SchemaVersionError`\n767: \n768: #### Merge Algorithm\n769: 1. Start with base metadata from file\n770: 2. For each field in CLI options:\n771:    - Override base value if option is provided\n772:    - Track which fields were overridden\n773: 3. Validate merged result\n774: 4. Return merged metadata with tracking info\n775: \n776: #### Backup Algorithm\n777: 1. Check if existing metadata file exists\n778: 2. If yes:\n779:    - Generate timestamp for backup filename\n780:    - Copy existing file to `.agentcube/metadata_history/`\n781:    - Check backup count and remove oldest if over limit\n782: 3. Save new metadata to main file\n783: \n784: #### Security Scan Algorithm\n785: 1. Define credential pattern regexes (API keys, passwords, tokens)\n786: 2. For each string field in metadata:\n787:    - Check against each pattern\n788:    - If match found, add field to results\n789: 3. Return list of fields with potential credentials\n790: 4. Log warnings and recommendations\n791: \n792: ---\n793: \n794: ## Technical Constraints\n795: \n796: ### Requirement: Language and dependencies\n797: \n798: System SHALL use Python 3.10+ and the following dependencies:\n799: \n800: **Dependencies:**\n801: - `pydantic>=2.0.0` for data validation and serialization\n802: - `pyyaml>=6.0` for YAML parsing and generation\n803: - `python-dateutil` for timestamp handling\n804: \n805: ### Requirement: File locations\n806: \n807: - MetadataService implementation: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n808: - AgentMetadata model: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n809: - Built-in templates: `agentcube/templates/`\n810: - User templates: `~/.agentcube/templates/`\n811: - Metadata history: `.agentcube/metadata_history/`\n812: - Primary metadata file: `agent_metadata.yaml`\n813: \n814: ### Requirement: Configuration\n815: \n816: - Backup count limit: Environment variable `AGENTCUBE_METADATA_HISTORY_LIMIT` (default: 10)\n817: - Template directories: Built-in + `~/.agentcube/templates/`\n818: - Current schema version: `\"1.0.0\"`\n819: \n820: ---\n821: \n822: ## Related Requirements\n823: \n824: - **AR-020:** CLI pack command (uses MetadataService)\n825: - **AR-021:** CLI build command (uses MetadataService)\n826: - **AR-022:** CLI publish command (uses MetadataService)\n827: - **AR-023:** CLI invoke/status commands (uses MetadataService)\n828: - **cli-toolkit/design.md:** Base design for MetadataService and AgentMetadata\n829: - **cli-toolkit/spec.md:** Base specification for metadata handling\n\n(End of file - total 829 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification: AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型\n\n## Module: `cmd/cli`\n\n## Language: Python\n\n## Size: M\n\n## Delta Overview\n\nEnhance the `MetadataService` and related data models to support improved metadata validation, persistence, manipulation, and management capabilities for the AgentCube CLI. This includes enhanced field validation, schema versioning, metadata templates, history tracking, and security scanning.\n\n---\n\n## REQ-001: Enhanced metadata validation\n\n### Requirement: Comprehensive field validation beyond type checking\n\nSystem SHALL provide comprehensive validation for metadata fields including format validation, context-aware validation, and security checks.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775875286479,"end":1775875286488}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775875286523,"sessionID":"ses_2859701edffeUJTW0BpL9de1DF","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6a65db001IXHWok2h4xHmGL","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7a6a5e1a0019sBC8YITY9dBBa","sessionID":"ses_2859701edffeUJTW0BpL9de1DF","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":40340,"input":211,"output":66,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":40063}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775875290300,"sessionID":"ses_2859701edffeUJTW0BpL9de1DF","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6a74b9001iM2Kq0RLeZvseU","messageID":"msg_d7a6a6611001G3TSKDiipWXA9E","sessionID":"ses_2859701edffeUJTW0BpL9de1DF","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875414844,"sessionID":"ses_2859701edffeUJTW0BpL9de1DF","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6c597e001aB19t4qIYL83P4","messageID":"msg_d7a6a6611001G3TSKDiipWXA9E","sessionID":"ses_2859701edffeUJTW0BpL9de1DF","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-63e1abde6eae4e5ba0b83988a4228545","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Specification: AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\n\n## Module: `cmd/cli`\n\n## Language: Python\n\n## Size: M\n\n## Delta Overview\n\nImplement dual provider support in the AgentCube CLI for deploying AI agents to Kubernetes: a standard provider using native Deployment and Service resources, and an AgentCube provider using the AgentRuntime custom resource (CR) for enhanced lifecycle management.\n\n---\n\n## REQ-001: Provider selection via CLI flag\n\n### Requirement: Provider parameter on commands\n\nSystem SHALL allow users to select the deployment target provider using the `--provider` flag on relevant commands (`publish`, `status`, `invoke`), with `agentcube` as the default provider.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- `--provider` flag accepts `k8s` or `agentcube` values\n- Default value is `agentcube` when not specified\n- Invalid provider values trigger error messages with valid options\n- Provider selection is propagated to runtime classes\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 1.1: Default provider value\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `publish` without the `--provider` flag\n- **WHEN** the Typer command callback runs\n- **THEN** the `provider` parameter SHALL default to `\"agentcube\"`\n\n#### Scenario 1.2: Valid provider selection - k8s\n- **GIVEN** the user specifies `--provider k8s`\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL route deployment operations to `KubernetesProvider`\n\n#### Scenario 1.3: Valid provider selection - agentcube\n- **GIVEN** the user specifies `--provider agentcube`\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL route deployment operations to `AgentCubeProvider`\n\n#### Scenario 1.4: Invalid provider value\n- **GIVEN** the user specifies `--provider invalid`\n- **WHEN** the command validates the provider parameter\n- **THEN** the system SHALL print an error message indicating valid options are `k8s` or `agentcube` and exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n## REQ-002: Kubernetes provider — Deployment creation\n\n### Requirement: Create Kubernetes Deployment resource\n\nSystem SHALL create a Kubernetes `Deployment` resource with configurable replicas, container port, and optional environment variables when using the `k8s` provider.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Creates Deployment with sanitized name from agent_name\n- Supports configurable replicas (default: 1)\n- Sets container image from image_url\n- Configures container port\n- Supports custom entrypoint command\n- Supports environment variables\n- Creates namespace if it doesn't exist\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 2.1: Minimal deployment creation\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s`, `replicas` is `1` (default), and no env_vars are provided\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` is called with `agent_name`, `image_url`, and `port`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create a Deployment with:\n  - `metadata.name` sanitized from `agent_name` via `_sanitize_name`\n  - `spec.replicas` set to `1`\n  - `spec.template.spec.containers[0].image` set to `image_url`\n  - `spec.template.spec.containers[0].ports[0].containerPort` set to `port`\n  - No environment variables in the container spec\n\n#### Scenario 2.2: Deployment with replicas and env vars\n- **GIVEN** `replicas` is `3` and `env_vars` is `{\"API_KEY\": \"secret\", \"DEBUG\": \"true\"}`\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create a Deployment with `spec.replicas` set to `3` and container `env` array containing both key-value pairs\n\n#### Scenario 2.3: Deployment with custom entrypoint\n- **GIVEN** `entrypoint` is `[\"python\", \"-u\", \"main.py\"]`\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` is called\n- **THEN** the container spec SHALL set `command` to the provided list\n\n#### Scenario 2.4: Name sanitization for K8s compliance\n- **GIVEN** `agent_name` is `my-agent-prod_v2.0`\n- **WHEN** `_sanitize_name` processes the name\n- **THEN** the result SHALL conform to Kubernetes naming rules (lowercase alphanumeric, hyphens, max 253 chars), e.g., `my-agent-prod-v2-0`\n\n#### Scenario 2.5: Namespace creation\n- **GIVEN** `namespace` is provided and does not exist\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider` initializes or deploys\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `_ensure_namespace` which creates the namespace if missing via the Kubernetes API\n\n---\n\n## REQ-003: Kubernetes provider — Service creation\n\n### Requirement: Create NodePort Service\n\nSystem SHALL create a NodePort Service exposing the deployment, with either a user-specified NodePort or an auto-assigned port in the valid range.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Creates Service of type NodePort\n- Supports user-specified NodePort (30000-32767)\n- Auto-assigns NodePort if not specified\n- Service selector matches deployment labels\n- Constructs service URL with NodePort\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 3.1: Service with user-specified NodePort\n- **GIVEN** `node_port` is `30080`\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider._create_service` is called\n- **THEN** the Service SHALL have `spec.ports[0].nodePort` set to `30080`\n\n#### Scenario 3.2: Service with auto-assigned NodePort\n- **GIVEN** `node_port` is `None`\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider._create_service` is called\n- **THEN** the Service SHALL omit the `nodePort` field, allowing Kubernetes to auto-assign a port in the 30000-32767 range\n\n#### Scenario 3.3: Service selector matches deployment\n- **GIVEN** the deployment was created with sanitized name `my-agent`\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider._create_service` runs\n- **THEN** the Service SHALL have `spec.selector` matching the deployment labels, typically including `app: my-agent`\n\n#### Scenario 3.4: Service URL construction\n- **GIVEN** the Service has `nodePort` `30080`\n- **WHEN** deployment completes successfully\n- **THEN** the result SHALL include `service_url` as `http://localhost:30080`\n\n---\n\n## REQ-004: Kubernetes provider — Rollout readiness\n\n### Requirement: Wait for deployment readiness\n\nSystem SHALL wait for the deployment to reach a ready state before considering the deployment complete, with a configurable timeout.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Polls deployment status every 2 seconds\n- Checks that readyReplicas equals replicas\n- Returns without error when all replicas are ready\n- Raises TimeoutError if deployment doesn't become ready within timeout\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 4.1: Successful rollout within timeout\n- **GIVEN** the deployment is created and pods become ready within 60 seconds\n- **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready(name=\"my-agent\", timeout=120)` is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return without error after all replicas are ready\n\n#### Scenario 4.2: Rollout timeout\n- **GIVEN** the deployment fails to become ready after 120 seconds\n- **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready(name=\"my-agent\", timeout=120)` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `TimeoutError` indicating the deployment did not become ready in time\n\n#### Scenario 4.3: Readiness polling\n- **GIVEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready` is polling\n- **WHEN** checking deployment status\n- **THEN** the system SHALL query the deployment status every 2 seconds and check that `status.readyReplicas` equals `spec.replicas`\n\n---\n\n## REQ-005: Kubernetes provider — Status retrieval\n\n### Requirement: Retrieve deployment status\n\nSystem SHALL retrieve and report deployment status including replica counts, pod states, and service URL when using the `k8s` provider.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Retrieves deployment status from Kubernetes API\n- Reports replica counts (replicas, ready_replicas, available_replicas)\n- Reports NodePort and service URL\n- Handles various deployment states (running, degraded, not_found)\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 5.1: Running deployment status\n- **GIVEN** a deployment with 3 replicas is running, all pods are ready, and service has NodePort 30080\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status(agent_name)` is called\n- **THEN** the result SHALL include:\n  - `status: \"running\"`\n  - `replicas: 3`\n  - `ready_replicas: 3`\n  - `available_replicas: 3`\n  - `node_port: 30080`\n  - `service_url: \"http://localhost:30080\"`\n\n#### Scenario 5.2: Deployment with unavailable pods\n- **GIVEN** a deployment with 2 replicas has 1 ready and 1 `CrashLoopBackOff`\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status` is called\n- **THEN** the result SHALL include `status: \"degraded\"` or `\"partial\"` and indicate the pod states\n\n#### Scenario 5.3: Non-existent deployment\n- **GIVEN** no deployment exists for `agent_name`\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status` is called\n- **THEN** the result SHALL include `status: \"not_found\"`\n\n---\n\n## REQ-006: Kubernetes provider — Deletion\n\n### Requirement: Delete deployment and service\n\nSystem SHALL delete both the Deployment and Service resources when removing an agent deployed via the `k8s` provider.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Deletes both Deployment and Service resources\n- Ignores 404 errors if resources don't exist\n- Returns success status with deployment and namespace information\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 6.1: Successful deletion\n- **GIVEN** a deployment and service exist for `agent_name`\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.delete_agent(agent_name)` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL delete both resources and return `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\": <sanitized-name>, \"namespace\": <namespace>}`\n\n#### Scenario 6.2: Partial deletion tolerance\n- **GIVEN** only the Service exists (Deployment already deleted)\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.delete_agent` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL delete the Service, ignore the 404 error for the Deployment, and return success\n\n---\n\n## REQ-007: AgentCube provider — AgentRuntime CR creation\n\n### Requirement: Create AgentRuntime custom resource\n\nSystem SHALL create or update an AgentRuntime custom resource in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group when using the `agentcube` provider.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Creates AgentRuntime CR with sanitized name\n- Sets image, port, sessionTimeout, maxSessionDuration\n- Supports readiness probe configuration\n- Supports custom environment variables\n- Auto-injects WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL and ROUTER_URL if not provided\n- Configures imagePullSecrets\n- Creates namespace if it doesn't exist\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 7.1: Minimal AgentRuntime creation\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` and metadata contains `image_url` and `port`\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create an AgentRuntime CR with:\n  - `metadata.name` sanitized from `agent_name`\n  - `spec.image` set to `image_url`\n  - `spec.port` set to `port`\n  - `spec.sessionTimeout` set to `\"15m\"`\n  - `spec.maxSessionDuration` set to `\"8h\"`\n\n#### Scenario 7.2: AgentRuntime with readiness probe\n- **GIVEN** metadata includes `readiness_probe_path: \"/health\"` and `readiness_probe_port: 8080`\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` is called\n- **THEN** the CR SHALL include `spec.readinessProbe` with `httpGet.path: \"/health\"` and `httpGet.port: 8080`\n\n#### Scenario 7.3: AgentRuntime with custom env vars\n- **GIVEN** `env_vars` is `{\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\": \"http://wm:8080\", \"ROUTER_URL\": \"http://router:8080\"}`\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` is called\n- **THEN** the CR SHALL include these in `spec.env`\n\n#### Scenario 7.4: Auto-inject WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL and ROUTER_URL\n- **GIVEN** `env_vars` is `None` but `workload_manager_url` and `router_url` parameters are provided\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL inject `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` and `ROUTER_URL` into `spec.env` from the parameters or environment variables\n\n#### Scenario 7.5: Image pull secret configuration\n- **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime CR is being created\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` runs\n- **THEN** the CR SHALL include `spec.imagePullSecrets: [{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n\n#### Scenario 7.6: Namespace creation for AgentCube provider\n- **GIVEN** `namespace` is provided and does not exist\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider` initializes or deploys\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `_ensure_namespace` which creates the namespace if missing\n\n---\n\n## REQ-008: AgentCube provider — AgentRuntime update\n\n### Requirement: Update existing AgentRuntime CR\n\nSystem SHALL support updating an existing AgentRuntime CR when re-publishing, using strategic merge patch.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Patches existing CR with new values\n- Preserves fields not being updated\n- Uses strategic merge patch for safe updates\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 8.1: Update existing CR\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime CR exists for `agent_name` with `image: \"old:v1\"`\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime` is called with a new `image_url: \"new:v2\"`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL patch the existing CR with the new image while preserving other fields\n\n#### Scenario 8.2: Update with readiness probe addition\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime CR without a readiness probe\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime` is called with `readiness_probe_path` and `readiness_probe_port`\n- **THEN** the patched CR SHALL include the new `readinessProbe` configuration\n\n---\n\n## REQ-009: AgentCube provider — Status retrieval\n\n### Requirement: Retrieve AgentRuntime status\n\nSystem SHALL retrieve AgentRuntime status from the CR's `status` field, reporting agent endpoint and runtime state.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Reads AgentRuntime CR from Kubernetes API\n- Reports status from CR's status field\n- Handles cases where status is not yet populated\n- Returns appropriate status for non-existent CRs\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 9.1: Running AgentRuntime with status\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime CR exists with `status.phase: \"Running\"` and `status.agentEndpoint: \"http://service:8080\"`\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` is called\n- **THEN** the result SHALL include:\n  - `status: \"running\"`\n  - `agent_endpoint: \"http://service:8080\"`\n  - `phase: \"Running\"`\n\n#### Scenario 9.2: AgentRuntime created but no status yet\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime CR exists but has no `status` field populated yet\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` is called\n- **THEN** the result SHALL include `status: \"created_no_status\"`\n\n#### Scenario 9.3: AgentRuntime not found\n- **GIVEN** no AgentRuntime CR exists for `agent_name`\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` is called\n- **THEN** the result SHALL include `status: \"not_found_in_k8s\"`\n\n---\n\n## REQ-010: Publish runtime — Provider routing\n\n### Requirement: Route publish operations to appropriate provider\n\nSystem SHALL route `publish` command operations to the appropriate provider class based on the `--provider` flag.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Routes to KubernetesProvider for --provider k8s\n- Routes to AgentCubeProvider for --provider agentcube\n- Prepares image appropriately for each provider\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 10.1: Publish with k8s provider\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `publish --provider k8s` with valid workspace and image\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `PublishRuntime._publish_k8s` which uses `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent`\n\n#### Scenario 10.2: Publish with agentcube provider\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `publish --provider agentcube` with valid workspace and image\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s` which uses `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime`\n\n#### Scenario 10.3: Publish image preparation for k8s\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s` and `image_url` is provided\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._prepare_image_for_publishing` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the provided `image_url` directly for Kubernetes deployment\n\n#### Scenario 10.4: Publish image preparation for agentcube\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` and `build_mode` is `local`\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._prepare_image_for_publishing` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL either push the local image to a registry or use the local image URL depending on configuration\n\n---\n\n## REQ-011: Status runtime — Provider routing\n\n### Requirement: Route status queries to appropriate provider\n\nSystem SHALL route `status` command queries to the appropriate provider class based on the `--provider` flag and deployment type.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Routes to KubernetesProvider for --provider k8s\n- Routes to AgentCubeProvider for --provider agentcube\n- Auto-detects provider from metadata when --provider not specified\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 11.1: Status with k8s provider\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `status --provider k8s`\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status` executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status` which uses `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status`\n\n#### Scenario 11.2: Status with agentcube provider\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `status --provider agentcube`\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status` executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` which uses `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime`\n\n#### Scenario 11.3: Auto-detect provider from metadata\n- **GIVEN** metadata has `k8s_deployment.type: \"AgentRuntime\"` and user runs `status` without `--provider`\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status` executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL automatically use the AgentCube provider path\n\n---\n\n## REQ-012: Invoke runtime — Provider routing\n\n### Requirement: Route invoke HTTP requests based on provider\n\nSystem SHALL route `invoke` command HTTP requests based on the agent's deployment type and provider, using appropriate URL patterns.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Routes to direct HTTP invocation for k8s provider\n- Routes to AgentCube invocation endpoint for agentcube provider\n- Rewrites URL for AgentRuntime deployments\n- Includes session header when available\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 12.1: Invoke with k8s provider\n- **GIVEN** the agent was deployed with `provider=k8s` and has `node_port: 30080`\n- **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs with `provider=\"k8s\"`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `_direct_http_invocation` targeting `http://localhost:30080` with the JSON payload\n\n#### Scenario 12.2: Invoke with agentcube provider and CR endpoint\n- **GIVEN** the agent was deployed with `provider=agentcube` and metadata has `agent_endpoint: \"http://service:8080\"`\n- **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs with `provider=\"agentcube\"`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` targeting the agent endpoint with session header\n\n#### Scenario 12.3: Invoke URL rewrite for AgentRuntime\n- **GIVEN** metadata has `k8s_deployment.type: \"AgentRuntime\"` and base endpoint from metadata\n- **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime._invoke_agent_via_agentcube` constructs the URL\n- **THEN** the system SHALL rewrite to `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n\n#### Scenario 12.4: Session header inclusion\n- **GIVEN** metadata contains `session_id: \"abc123\"`\n- **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` sends the request\n- **THEN** the HTTP headers SHALL include `X-Agentcube-Session-Id: abc123`\n\n---\n\n## REQ-013: Error handling for provider operations\n\n### Requirement: Provide clear error messages for provider failures\n\nSystem SHALL provide clear error messages for provider-specific failures, including K8s API errors, missing CRDs, and invalid configurations.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Surfaces Kubernetes client initialization failures\n- Detects missing AgentRuntime CRD\n- Validates NodePort range\n- Validates required AgentCube URLs\n- Provides user-friendly error messages\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 13.1: Kubernetes client initialization failure\n- **GIVEN** the kubeconfig is invalid or cluster is unreachable\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider` or `AgentCubeProvider` initializes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise a descriptive error indicating Kubernetes connection failure and suggest checking kubeconfig\n\n#### Scenario 13.2: AgentRuntime CRD not installed\n- **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime CRD is not installed in the cluster\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` attempts to create the CR\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise an error indicating the CRD is not found and suggest installing the AgentCube operator\n\n#### Scenario 13.3: Invalid NodePort range\n- **GIVEN** `node_port` is `40000` (outside 30000-32767)\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider._create_service` attempts to create the service\n- **THEN** Kubernetes API SHALL reject with validation error, which the system SHALL surface as a user-friendly message\n\n#### Scenario 13.4: Missing required AgentCube URLs\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` and metadata lacks `router_url` or `workload_manager_url`\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s` validates prerequisites\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` requiring both fields in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n---\n\n## REQ-014: Metadata updates after deployment\n\n### Requirement: Update metadata with deployment information\n\nSystem SHALL update workspace metadata with deployment information after successful publish operations, varying by provider.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Updates k8s_deployment field for k8s provider\n- Updates k8s_deployment and agent_id for agentcube provider\n- Preserves other metadata fields\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 14.1: K8s provider metadata update\n- **GIVEN** a deployment succeeds with `node_port: 30080`\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._update_publish_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** metadata SHALL be updated with:\n  - `k8s_deployment.type: \"Deployment\"`\n  - `k8s_deployment.name: <sanitized-name>`\n  - `k8s_deployment.namespace: <namespace>`\n  - `k8s_deployment.node_port: 30080`\n  - `k8s_deployment.service_url: \"http://localhost:30080\"`\n\n#### Scenario 14.2: AgentCube provider metadata update\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime CR is created successfully\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._update_publish_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** metadata SHALL be updated with:\n  - `k8s_deployment.type: \"AgentRuntime\"`\n  - `k8s_deployment.name: <sanitized-name>`\n  - `k8s_deployment.namespace: <namespace>`\n  - `agent_id: <cr-name>` (optional, if assigned by controller)\n\n---\n\n## REQ-015: Namespace parameter handling\n\n### Requirement: Support namespace specification and defaults\n\nSystem SHALL support explicit namespace specification via `--namespace` flag for all provider operations, with intelligent defaults.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Supports explicit namespace via --namespace flag\n- Defaults to \"default\" namespace when not specified\n- Maintains namespace consistency across commands\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 15.1: Explicit namespace for publish\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `publish --namespace production`\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL deploy to the `production` namespace\n\n#### Scenario 15.2: Default namespace when omitted\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `publish` without `--namespace`\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `default` namespace for both providers\n\n#### Scenario 15.3: Namespace consistency across commands\n- **GIVEN** an agent was published to namespace `staging`\n- **WHEN** user runs `status` or `invoke` without `--namespace`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL read the namespace from metadata's `k8s_deployment.namespace` field\n\n---\n\n## Data Model Changes\n\n### `KubernetesProvider` class\n\n```python\nclass KubernetesProvider:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n    ) -> None: ...\n\n    def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n\n    def deploy_agent(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        image_url: str,\n        port: int,\n        entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n        replicas: int = 1,\n        node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n        env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n\n    def _create_deployment(\n        self,\n        name: str,\n        image_url: str,\n        port: int,\n        entrypoint: Optional[str],\n        replicas: int,\n        env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n\n    def _create_service(self, name: str, port: int, node_port: Optional[int]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n\n    def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None: ...\n\n    def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n\n    def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n\n    def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n```\n\n### `AgentCubeProvider` class\n\n```python\nclass AgentCubeProvider:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n    ) -> None: ...\n\n    def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n\n    def deploy_agent_runtime(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        image_url: str,\n        port: int,\n        entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n        env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n        readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n\n    def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n\n    def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n```\n\n### CR API constants\n\n```python\nAGENTRUNTIME_GROUP = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"\nAGENTRUNTIME_VERSION = \"v1alpha1\"\nAGENTRUNTIME_PLURAL = \"agentruntimes\"\n```\n\n### `PublishRuntime` enhancements\n\n```python\nclass PublishRuntime:\n    def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n    def _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None: ...\n```\n\n### `StatusRuntime` enhancements\n\n```python\nclass StatusRuntime:\n    def get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n```\n\n### `InvokeRuntime` enhancements\n\n```python\nclass InvokeRuntime:\n    def invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Any: ...\n    def _validate_invoke_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Tuple[Any, str, str]: ...\n    async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(self, agent_id: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], endpoint: str, workspace_path: Path) -> Any: ...\n    async def _direct_http_invocation(self, endpoint: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], workspace_path: Path) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Requirements\n\n### Unit Test Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario UT-1: Test KubernetesProvider deployment\n- **GIVEN** a mocked Kubernetes API client\n- **WHEN** tests run\n- **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n  - Minimal deployment creation\n  - Deployment with replicas and env vars\n  - Deployment with custom entrypoint\n  - Name sanitization\n  - Namespace creation\n\n#### Scenario UT-2: Test KubernetesProvider service\n- **GIVEN** a mocked Kubernetes API client\n- **WHEN** tests run\n- **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n  - Service with user-specified NodePort\n  - Service with auto-assigned NodePort\n  - Service selector matching deployment\n  - Service URL construction\n\n#### Scenario UT-3: Test KubernetesProvider status and deletion\n- **GIVEN** a mocked Kubernetes API client\n- **WHEN** tests run\n- **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n  - Running deployment status\n  - Deployment with unavailable pods\n  - Non-existent deployment\n  - Successful deletion\n  - Partial deletion tolerance\n\n#### Scenario UT-4: Test AgentCubeProvider\n- **GIVEN** a mocked Kubernetes API client\n- **WHEN** tests run\n- **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n  - Minimal AgentRuntime creation\n  - AgentRuntime with readiness probe\n  - AgentRuntime with custom env vars\n  - Auto-inject WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL and ROUTER_URL\n  - Image pull secret configuration\n  - AgentRuntime update\n  - Status retrieval scenarios\n\n#### Scenario UT-5: Test provider routing\n- **GIVEN** mocked provider instances\n- **WHEN** tests run\n- **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n  - Publish routing to k8s provider\n  - Publish routing to agentcube provider\n  - Status routing to k8s provider\n  - Status routing to agentcube provider\n  - Auto-detect provider from metadata\n\n#### Scenario UT-6: Test error handling\n- **GIVEN** various error conditions\n- **WHEN** tests run\n- **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n  - Kubernetes client initialization failure\n  - AgentRuntime CRD not installed\n  - Invalid NodePort range\n  - Missing required AgentCube URLs\n\n### Integration Test Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario IT-1: End-to-end k8s provider workflow\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster with kubectl configured\n- **WHEN** user runs:\n  1. `pack --agent-name my-k8s-agent --provider k8s`\n  2. `build`\n  3. `publish --provider k8s --node-port 30080`\n  4. `status --provider k8s`\n  5. `invoke --provider k8s --payload '{\"test\": \"data\"}'`\n- **THEN** each operation SHALL:\n  - Create Deployment and Service\n  - Report correct status\n  - Successfully invoke the agent\n  - Clean up on deletion\n\n#### Scenario IT-2: End-to-end agentcube provider workflow\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster with AgentRuntime CRD installed\n- **WHEN** user runs:\n  1. `pack --agent-name my-ac-agent --provider agentcube`\n  2. `build`\n  3. `publish --provider agentcube`\n  4. `status --provider agentcube`\n  5. `invoke --provider agentcube --payload '{\"test\": \"data\"}'`\n- **THEN** each operation SHALL:\n  - Create AgentRuntime CR\n  - Report correct status\n  - Successfully invoke the agent\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n### Functional Acceptance Criteria - Provider Selection\n\n- [ ] --provider flag accepts k8s and agentcube values\n- [ ] Default provider is agentcube\n- [ ] Invalid provider values trigger error with valid options\n- [ ] Provider selection propagated to runtime classes\n\n### Functional Acceptance Criteria - Kubernetes Provider\n\n- [ ] Creates Deployment with correct configuration\n- [ ] Creates Service of type NodePort\n- [ ] Supports user-specified and auto-assigned NodePort\n- [ ] Waits for deployment readiness with timeout\n- [ ] Retrieves deployment status correctly\n- [ ] Deletes Deployment and Service\n- [ ] Sanitizes names for K8s compliance\n\n### Functional Acceptance Criteria - AgentCube Provider\n\n- [ ] Creates AgentRuntime CR with correct configuration\n- [ ] Supports readiness probe configuration\n- [ ] Supports custom environment variables\n- [ ] Auto-injects WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL and ROUTER_URL\n- [ ] Configures imagePullSecrets\n- [ ] Updates existing AgentRuntime CR\n- [ ] Retrieves AgentRuntime status correctly\n\n### Functional Acceptance Criteria - Provider Routing\n\n- [ ] Publish routes to correct provider\n- [ ] Status routes to correct provider\n- [ ] Invoke routes to correct provider\n- [ ] Auto-detects provider from metadata\n\n### Functional Acceptance Criteria - Error Handling\n\n- [ ] Kubernetes client initialization failures surfaced\n- [ ] Missing AgentRuntime CRD detected\n- [ ] Invalid NodePort range validated\n- [ ] Missing required AgentCube URLs validated\n\n### Functional Acceptance Criteria - Metadata Updates\n\n- [ ] K8s provider updates k8s_deployment field\n- [ ] AgentCube provider updates k8s_deployment and agent_id\n- [ ] Other metadata fields preserved\n\n### Functional Acceptance Criteria - Namespace Handling\n\n- [ ] Explicit namespace via --namespace flag works\n- [ ] Default namespace is \"default\"\n- [ ] Namespace consistency maintained across commands\n\n### Non-Functional Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Provider operations complete within reasonable time\n- [ ] Error messages are clear and actionable\n- [ ] Unit tests cover all new methods with >= 90% coverage\n- [ ] Integration tests cover end-to-end workflows\n- [ ] Code follows existing patterns in cli-toolkit/design.md\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Key Components\n\n1. **KubernetesProvider** (`agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`)\n   - Implements standard Kubernetes Deployment and Service management\n   - Handles name sanitization, namespace management, readiness checks\n\n2. **AgentCubeProvider** (`agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`)\n   - Implements AgentRuntime CR management\n   - Auto-injects required environment variables\n   - Configures imagePullSecrets\n\n3. **PublishRuntime** (`agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`)\n   - Enhanced with provider routing\n   - Separate methods for k8s and agentcube deployment paths\n\n4. **StatusRuntime** (`agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`)\n   - Enhanced with provider routing\n   - Separate methods for k8s and agentcube status retrieval\n\n5. **InvokeRuntime** (`agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`)\n   - Enhanced with provider-specific URL construction\n   - Session header handling\n\n### Key Algorithms\n\n#### Provider Factory Pattern\n```python\ndef get_provider(provider_type: str, namespace: str, verbose: bool) -> Union[KubernetesProvider, AgentCubeProvider]:\n    if provider_type == \"k8s\":\n        return KubernetesProvider(namespace=namespace, verbose=verbose)\n    elif provider_type == \"agentcube\":\n        return AgentCubeProvider(namespace=namespace, verbose=verbose)\n    else:\n        raise ValueError(f\"Invalid provider: {provider_type}\")\n```\n\n#### Name Sanitization\n```python\ndef _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str:\n    # Convert to lowercase, replace invalid chars with hyphens, truncate to 253 chars\n    sanitized = re.sub(r'[^a-z0-9-]', '-', name.lower())\n    sanitized = sanitized.strip('-')\n    return sanitized[:253]\n```\n\n#### Metadata-Driven Provider Detection\n```python\ndef detect_provider_from_metadata(metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n    if metadata.k8s_deployment and metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"type\") == \"AgentRuntime\":\n        return \"agentcube\"\n    return \"k8s\"  # or default\n```\n\n### Technical Constraints\n\n### Requirement: Language and dependencies\n\nSystem SHALL use Python 3.10+ and the following dependencies:\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `kubernetes>=28.0.0` for Kubernetes API client\n- `pydantic>=2.0.0` for data validation (already in base)\n- `pyyaml>=6.0` for YAML parsing (already in base)\n\n### Requirement: File locations\n\n- KubernetesProvider implementation: `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n- AgentCubeProvider implementation: `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n- Runtime enhancements: `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`, `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`, `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n\n### Requirement: Configuration\n\n- Default namespace: `\"default\"`\n- Default NodePort: auto-assigned by Kubernetes (30000-32767)\n- Default replicas: `1`\n- Deployment readiness timeout: `120` seconds\n- AgentRuntime sessionTimeout: `\"15m\"`\n- AgentRuntime maxSessionDuration: `\"8h\"`\n\n---\n\n## Related Requirements\n\n- **AR-022:** CLI publish command (uses provider system)\n- **AR-023:** CLI invoke/status commands (use provider system)\n- **cli-toolkit/design.md:** Base design for KubernetesProvider and AgentCubeProvider\n- **cli-toolkit/spec.md:** Base specification for provider operations\n- **deployment/client-go.md:** Reference for AgentRuntime CR API","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775875414532,"end":1775875414840}}}}
